---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import '../styles/how-it-works.css';
const stages = [
  ['01','Identity','Link every action to an authenticated developer, agent, repository, and session.'],
  ['02','Intent','Capture what the agent is trying to change before execution begins.'],
  ['03','Policy','Evaluate affected scope against protected paths, standards, and approval rules.'],
  ['04','Enforcement','Permit valid work or block unsafe actions before they reach the target.'],
  ['05','Evidence','Seal the decision, context, and outcome into a reviewable evidence record.'],
];
const controls = [
  ['While the agent works','Keep specialized agents inside approved responsibilities and scope.'],
  ['Before file write','Stop protected-path, secret, dependency, and architecture violations early.'],
  ['At commit','Verify authorship, tests, policy state, and the exact resulting change.'],
  ['Before production','Require the right evidence and approvals before code can ship.'],
];
---
<SiteLayout title="How Mault Works | Govern AI-Written Code" description="See how Mault binds identity, captures agent intent, enforces policy before execution, and produces evidence for every AI coding action." canonical="/how-it-works/">
  <div class="hiw-page">
    <header class="hiw-hero"><div class="shell hiw-hero-grid"><div><p class="eyebrow">How it works</p><h1>Your standards ship.<br/><span class="gradient-text">Not suggestions.</span></h1><p class="lede">Mault governs AI-written code at the moment of action. Identity, intent, policy, enforcement, and evidence stay connected from prompt to production.</p><div class="hero-actions"><a class="button" href="/pilot/">Start a pilot</a><a class="button button-secondary" href="#decision">Run a decision</a></div></div><div class="hiw-console"><div class="terminal-bar"><i></i><i></i><i></i><span>mault / policy engine</span></div><code><b>$</b> mault evaluate --action write<br/><span>identity</span> developer@company<br/><span>agent</span> cursor<br/><span>target</span> src/auth/session.ts<br/><span>policy</span> production<br/><strong>PERMITTED · EVIDENCE SEALED</strong></code></div></div></header>
    <section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">The gap</p><h2>AI adoption is everywhere. The ROI isn’t.</h2></div><p>Ungoverned coding agents move quickly, but rework, review debt, unclear authorship, and missing evidence erase the velocity they promise.</p></div><div class="hiw-compare"><article><span>Without Mault</span><h3>Speed without control</h3><ul><li>Agent actions cross unclear boundaries</li><li>Senior engineers absorb review debt</li><li>Standards are suggestions after the fact</li><li>Evidence is assembled manually</li></ul></article><article class="is-governed"><span>With Mault</span><h3>Velocity you can prove</h3><ul><li>Every action stays attributable</li><li>Unsafe work is blocked before impact</li><li>Standards execute as policy</li><li>Evidence is captured automatically</li></ul></article></div></div></section>
    <section class="section hiw-chain"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">The decision chain</p><h2>One control plane. Every agent action.</h2></div><p>Each decision moves through five deterministic stages. Select a stage to inspect what Mault captures.</p></div><div class="hiw-chain-grid"><div class="hiw-stage-list">{stages.map(([number,title,copy], index) => <button type="button" class:list={{active:index===0}} data-hiw-stage data-title={title} data-copy={copy} aria-pressed={index===0?'true':'false'}><span>{number}</span><strong>{title}</strong><small>Inspect →</small></button>)}</div><aside class="hiw-inspector" data-hiw-inspector><p class="eyebrow">Verified control input</p><h3>Identity</h3><p>Link every action to an authenticated developer, agent, repository, and session.</p><div><span>developer</span><code>authenticated</code><span>agent</span><code>attributed</code><span>session</span><code>bound</code></div></aside></div></div></section>
    <section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">Continuous enforcement</p><h2>Govern from keystroke to production.</h2></div><p>Mault applies the same standards across the workflow instead of waiting for a reviewer to discover problems at the end.</p></div><div class="hiw-controls">{controls.map(([title,copy],i)=><article data-reveal><span>0{i+1}</span><h3>{title}</h3><p>{copy}</p></article>)}</div></div></section>
    <section class="section hiw-simulator" id="decision"><div class="shell hiw-sim-grid"><div><p class="eyebrow">Try the control plane</p><h2>Run a policy decision.</h2><p>Choose an agent action to see how Mault evaluates intent and scope before execution.</p></div><div class="hiw-sim" data-hiw-sim><div class="hiw-sim-actions"><button type="button" data-result="permit" class="active">Update approved source</button><button type="button" data-result="block">Write production secret</button><button type="button" data-result="block">Bypass required tests</button></div><div class="hiw-result permit" data-hiw-result><span>DECISION / PERMITTED</span><code>policy: production<br/>scope: src/components/*<br/>controls: satisfied<br/>evidence: sealed</code><p>Approved work proceeds with identity and evidence attached.</p></div></div></div></section>
    <section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="section-head"><div><p class="eyebrow">The result</p><h2>Your development team. At AI speed. Without the risk.</h2></div><p>Governance removes rework and uncertainty without replacing the tools engineers already use.</p></div><div class="cards-3"><article class="card"><span class="card-index">01</span><h3>Less review debt</h3><p>Catch preventable agent mistakes before they land in a senior engineer’s queue.</p></article><article class="card"><span class="card-index">02</span><h3>Complete attribution</h3><p>Know who initiated every action, which agent acted, and what policy decided.</p></article><article class="card"><span class="card-index">03</span><h3>Evidence by default</h3><p>Turn each governed action into proof for engineering, security, and compliance.</p></article></div></div></section>
    <section class="cta"><div class="shell cta-box"><p class="eyebrow">See Mault inside your stack</p><h2>Govern the code your AI writes.</h2><p>Start with one high-value workflow and prove control in 45 days.</p><a class="button" href="/pilot/">Explore the pilot</a></div></section>
  </div>
  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-hiw-stage]').forEach((button)=>button.addEventListener('click',()=>{const inspector=document.querySelector('[data-hiw-inspector]');document.querySelectorAll('[data-hiw-stage]').forEach((item)=>{item.classList.remove('active');item.setAttribute('aria-pressed','false')});button.classList.add('active');button.setAttribute('aria-pressed','true');if(inspector){const h3=inspector.querySelector('h3'),p=inspector.querySelector(':scope > p:nth-of-type(2)');if(h3)h3.textContent=button.getAttribute('data-title');if(p)p.textContent=button.getAttribute('data-copy')}}));
    const outcomes={permit:['DECISION / PERMITTED','policy: production<br/>scope: src/components/*<br/>controls: satisfied<br/>evidence: sealed','Approved work proceeds with identity and evidence attached.'],block:['DECISION / BLOCKED','policy: protected boundary<br/>scope: denied<br/>controls: violated<br/>evidence: sealed','The unsafe action stops before reaching the protected target.']};
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-hiw-sim] button').forEach((button)=>button.addEventListener('click',()=>{const result=document.querySelector('[data-hiw-result]'),key=button.getAttribute('data-result')==='permit'?'permit':'block',data=outcomes[key];document.querySelectorAll('[data-hiw-sim] button').forEach((item)=>item.classList.remove('active'));button.classList.add('active');if(result){result.className='hiw-result '+key;const span=result.querySelector('span'),code=result.querySelector('code'),p=result.querySelector('p');if(span)span.textContent=data[0];if(code)code.innerHTML=data[1];if(p)p.textContent=data[2]}}));
  </script>
</SiteLayout>
<style>.hiw-console code span,.hiw-console .terminal-bar span{color:#aab4ab!important}.hiw-controls article>span{color:var(--green)!important}</style>
